From: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>
Date: 2026-05-13
Subject: [PATCH] ps4_mts: v93 — netdev wrapper (alloc_etherdev + NAPI + xmit/RX)

v91 brought the PS4 Baikal MTS MAC's BAR+0x04 bit 0 to latch for the
first time (LINK UP 1000Mb/s Full Duplex confirmed both sides with
host Realtek RTL8153 USB-Ethernet partner).  But the driver was
intentionally phase-1: no net_device, no DMA, just PHY/MAC bringup.
`ip link` showed only lo/wlan0/ap0/ap1 — no mts0/eth0.

v93 wraps the working phase-1 init with a real netdev:
  - devm_alloc_etherdev_mqs(sizeof(struct mts), 1 TX, 1 RX queue)
  - register_netdev (LAST in probe — no half-initialized iface visible)
  - ndo_open  — init rings, kick engines, napi_enable
  - ndo_stop  — release skbs, napi_disable (keeps MAC engines running
                so subsequent open re-uses the existing link state)
  - ndo_start_xmit — TX descriptor write + BAR+0x34 |= 4 kick
  - ndo_get_stats64 — counters from BAR+0x118/0x128/0x12c
  - NAPI poll — drain TX completion + RX ring + refill
  - ISR rewired to schedule NAPI on bits 0x40|0x80|0x22

Descriptor layout VERIFIED by hermes Ghidra dig (saved at
checkpoint/docs/research/hermes+v93_descriptor_format.md) of Orbis
12.02 mts_init_rings_kick + mts_tx_complete + mts_rx_unwrap_one +
mts_rx_process + mts_intr.  CRITICAL hermes corrections vs my initial
draft (caught before staging per CLAUDE.md sanity-check rule):

  1. OWN bit semantics are INVERTED.  Driver CLEARS bit 31 to hand
     descriptor to HW; HW SETS bit 31 on completion.  Opposite of
     typical descriptor designs.
  2. TX kick register is BAR+0x34 (not BAR+0x38 as earlier labelled);
     RX refill kick at BAR+0x38.  Engine-enable bit 0 works at both,
     packet-path kick is bit 2.
  3. TX descriptor needs SOF (bit 29) + EOF (bit 28) on single-segment
     frames; TX length is 16-bit in low bits, not 11-bit like RX.
  4. RX buffer size is 0x600 (1536 bytes), not 2048.
  5. TX "free" descriptors marked by aux0 = 0xffff0000 sentinel
     (per Orbis init); driver tests this to distinguish "HW completed
     real frame" from "descriptor was never submitted".
  6. RX bit 17 is checksum status, NOT "packet valid" — completion
     condition is just OWN=1 + length>0.

References:
  - checkpoint/docs/research/hermes+v93_descriptor_format.md  (161 lines)
  - checkpoint/docs/research/deepseek+v93_phase1_to_phase3_diff.md (339)
  - checkpoint/docs/research/glm+v93_netdev_template.md (488)
  - checkpoint/docs/research/kimi+v93_minimum_netdev.md (346)

After this patch, expected behavior:
  - `ip link show mts0` shows the interface (state UNKNOWN until
    ip link set up).
  - `ip link set mts0 up` → carrier comes ON via netif_carrier_on
    (since v91 link is already up at probe time).
  - `ip addr add 10.0.0.2/24 dev mts0; ping 10.0.0.1` should work
    if host RTL8153 is on the same subnet.

UNTESTED — descriptor format hermes-verified but hand-off ordering,
endian handling, kick timing not yet validated on hardware.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
